*vpopmail-5.2.1-r7 (02 Oct 2003)

  02 Oct 2003; Robin H. Johnson <robbat2@gentoo.org> vpopmail-5.2.1-r7.ebuild:
  bump version to ensure mysql fix is in place

  02 Oct 2003; Robin H. Johnson <robbat2@gentoo.org> vpopmail-5.2.1-r6.ebuild:
  fix typo bug #30203

  01 Oct 2003; Robin H. Johnson <robbat2@gentoo.org> vpopmail-5.2.1-r6.ebuild:
  bump to x86

  25 Sep 2003; <solar@gentoo.org> vpopmail-5.2.1-r6.ebuild:
  new local use flag clearpasswd that enables clear text passwd storage of
  vpasswd files. This changes the default behavior to now not store cleartext by
  default. closes bug 20127

  06 Aug 2003; Robin H. Johnson <robbat2@gentoo.org> vpopmail-5.2.1-r6.ebuild,
  files/vpopmail-5.2.1-showall.patch:
  fix bug #23876

  06 Aug 2003; Robin H. Johnson <robbat2@gentoo.org> vpopmail-5.2.1-r6.ebuild,
  files/99vpopmail:
  obsolete piles of symlinks, as only root needs to access the binaries in
  /var/vpopmail/bin, so we do it via env.d instead, along with a CONFIG_PROTECT
  entry for their user data

